                                                                Tailwind CSS
                                                                ************



Adding Tailwind to HTML:
------------------------
    * using CDN
            
        or
            
    * 2nd method:
        step-1) Install Node
        step-2) Open Terminal and Run commands:
                * node -v 
                * npm -v 
                * npm install -D tailwindcss postcss autoprefixer vite
                * npx tailwindcss init -p
                
        step-3) Install tailwind css intellisence extension in vs code.
        step-4) Add "*" inside content in tailwind.config.js file.
        step-5) Add "scripts": { "start": "vite"}, in package.json file.
        step-6) create main.css and paste below commands there:
                @tailwind base;
                @tailwind components;
                @tailwind utilities;
                
        step-7) link main.css to html file.
        step-8) To start live server use command: 
                * npm run start
                * then ctrl + click on link









Note:
-----
    -- Refer Tailwind css MDN.




































